	<h3>Smart Webbing?</h3><a href="http://www.acm.org/technews/articles/2004-6/0507f.html#item19">ACM News Service: Spinning a Smarter Web</a>.&nbsp; Artificial intelligence researcher Sheila McIlraith of the University of Toronto "notes that the Semantic Web currently lacks a business case.&nbsp; Even if one were to emerge, there is no guarantee that the Semantic Web will become universal.&nbsp; Other challenges facing the Semantic Web include issues over privacy, and how agents can determine the trustworthiness of information when confronted by conflicting data."&nbsp; It is also noted that there is major funding in Europe and that the Semantic Web is taken very seriously there.<br>
