	<h3>The nitty-gritty of how not to use encryption</h3><a href="http://www.cse.ucsd.edu/users/tkohno/papers/WinZip/">Attacking and repairing the WinZip "Advanced Encryption" scheme</a>.&nbsp; Here's the skinny on the way software can end up using encryption in an insecure way.&nbsp; Here's detailed information that is representative of the kinds of diligence it takes to incorporate an encryption system into a product or to use one that has been provided.&nbsp; There are caveats around the application of almost every cryptographic technique, and one should be careful to know what they are and to safeguard against misuse of the technique.&nbsp; Finally, it is important to keep asking about the threat one is attempting to mitigate and questioning how a particular security practice actually applies to that.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid at <a href="http://orcmid.com/blog/2004/05/attacking-and-repairing-winzip.asp">5/16/2004 07:03:20 PM</a></span>
	  
